@node "Einleitung" "Introduction"

 So here it is... the DataBox @{" SpeedDragon " link "databox" 0} from Hagenuk.
 Very quick it is connected to the Amiga and ready to use.
 Your analog telephones are connected very easy too.
 But the you have to configure the DataBox.  

 Long strings of numbers you have to type to your telephone.
 Would it be nice to have an Wondows-PC now to use the configuration
 software from it.
 
 Since DragonTools there is no longer need for a PC.
 You can use your Amiga to configure your DataBox.
 All you need are this  @{" Requirements " link "Voraussetzungen" 0}.
@endnode

@node "Rechtliches" "Copyright"

 DragonTools is Freeware. 

 You are allow to forward the complete programpackage for free.
 The copyright is owned by the @{" Programer " link "Programmierer" 0}.

 DragonTools is provided "as is".

 Changings of the program and/or the Wizard-files are prohibited.
 For transferring you are allowed to compress the program.
@endnode

@node "Voraussetzungen" "Requirements"

 To use DragonTools you need the following:

  - An Amiga with Amiga-OS 3.x
  - 1MB ChipRAM
  - 2MB FastRAM
  - Hagenuk's @{" DataBox " link "databox" 0} "Speed Dragon"
  - installed "wizard.library" (see @{" Installation " link "Installation" 0})

 recommended is:
  
  - serial-multi-I/O-Card
  - faster Processor
  - much more of RAM :)



 Note: With a different one of the "wizard.library" DragonTools 
          mabe run under AMiga-OS 2.x (not tested)
@endnode

@node "Haftung" "Disclaimer"

 I can give no warranty, that DragonTools is completly bugfree.
 Use DragonTools on your own risk !

 THERE IS NO WARRANTY FOR THE PROGRAM, TO THE EXTENT PERMITTED BY
 APPLICABLE LAW.
@endnode

@node "Besondere_Merkmale" "Special features"

 Little programs sometimes have nice features too:

   - grafical user interface
   
   - don't need MUI

   - easy way of choosing serial-ports

   - runs speeds from 300 up to 115200 Baud

   - makes you able to change the speed of the "DataBox"

   - confiruring default-settings,
     call-redirection and MAN-hiding
@endnode

@node "Schnelleinstieg" "Quickstartg"

 Short and quick to the finish
 -----------------------------

    - copy "wizard.library" to "libs:"
    - start "DragonTools"
    - press the button "Preferences"
    - choose your serial driver
    - let the program search the DataBox
    - if the DataBox was found, save preferences and close the window
    - press one of these buttons:
    
         - "Confirure DataBox" for preferences
         - "MSN-hiding"        for hide/unhide MSN's
         - "rate-counter"      for check and reset rate-counter
         - "call-routing"      to redirect incoming calls



 Note:     If you updated from V1.x to V2.x you have to define the preferences
           completely new.

           Each version of DragonTools needs a special version of the german
           catalog-file. Normaly it will be found in "PROGDIR:Catalogs/".
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"

 To install you only have to copy the "wizard.library" to your
 "libs:"-drawer. That you could do with "copy" or use my little
 installer-script.

 The main-program can be placed everywhere on your HD.
 
 Note:  - In the program-drawer are files without an icon.
          Copy these files too, because "DragonTools" need them !

        - "DragonTools" could NOT be used from CD-ROM, because of
          program-savings.

