@node "DataBox" "Speed Dragon"

 Some words about the DataBox "Speed Dragon"
 -------------------------------------------
 The DataBox is a ISDN-Terminal with an integrated active ISDN-modem.
 This terminal combines the ISDN-features with the cheap prices for
 analog devices.

 The DataBox can installed at the wallet and on a table, too.
 The measures are 21x17x6 cm.
 
 The features:

  - 3 A/B - changer to connect analog devices
  
  - LC-Display for costs, calls, incoming calls ...
    There is no longer need for expensive ISDN-devices.
  
  - integrated active ISDN-modem
  
  - AT-command-interpreter (modem-emulation)
  
  - flash-Rom for system-software.
    Updating easily by using a terminal-program

  - comes with all cables and adapters you need

  - Manual and CD-ROM (software only for PC and Mac)


 The used AT-commands to configure the DataBox comes in a text-file
 on the CD-ROM.

 Before the first installation, the speed of the DataBox is set to 9600 Baud.
 The DataBox not automatically modify its speed.
 You have to do this with the AT-commands.

 My program "DragonTools" makes it possible to modify the speed very easy.


  Why is the DataBox,that costs ca. 500,-DM so cheap ?
 -----------------------------------------------------
 this is easy to explain:

    simple ISDN-terminal                350,-DM
    ISDN-telephone (for ISDN-features)  250,-DM
    ISDN-modem or ISDN-card             200,-DM to 400,-DM

 All this devices together are much expensive than the DataBox.
@endnode

@node "bfehler" "known bugs"

 List of known bugs
 ------------------

 - it seems, that DragonTools does NOT work with BaudBandit.device 

 - MSNs could NOT defined more than one time.
   This is NO bug.
   
 - You should use firmware 2.5 at least.
   Older firmwares can have timing-errors.

 - The font-requester is simple.
   That could be fixed in future versions.
@endnode

@node "knock" "knocking"

 What is "knocking"?
 --------------------
 
 When you are calling with somebody and for the line you use you have
 activated the "knocking"-feature you will hear a special sound, when 
 somebody else calls this number.

 Now you can change between both callers.

  1. By perssing the "R"-button  at your telephone.
     Now you are connected to the second caller and the first call will be hold.

  2. You end the first call and hang up. 
     Now your telephone rings and wehn you hook on, you are connected to
     the second caller.
@endnode

@node "fwupdate" "firmware-updates"

 @{fg shine}DataBox firmware@{fg text}
 ----------------

 The  firmware  (systemsoftware of the DataBox) 
 is provided by Fa. Hagenuk.

 Actual version you can get from http://www.hagenuk.com/support/index.htm

 @{fg shine}firmware-update@{fg text}
 ---------------
 Up to today there is no Amiga-program to make a firmware-update.
 
 What you need is a actual firmware-file and a terminal-program.
 
 Firmware-files should end at ".BIN" and 460 to 500 kByte long.

 First you should check

  - that you have a correct firmware for your DataBox
  - the new one truely is newer than your used firmware
  - you have a copy of your old firmware
 
 When you use "TERM" here are the settings:

    preferences/serial
    ------------------
    - set baudrate and serial.driver
    - set protocol to RTS/CTS

    preferences/protocols
    ---------------------
    - set Binary-protocol to "XPR-library"
    - send = xprxmodem.library
    - no signature
    - settings: CRC no, 1k-Blocks yes

 Type in the following line and hit return

    ATZ0

 The DataBox sould send "OK"

 Now type this

    ATI0 

 and
    
    ATI4

 Check the appearings datas


 @{fg shine}XModem-transfer@{fg text}
 ------------------
 Type in
 
    AT UPX

 The coming question you answer with "y" before 20 seconds to begin
 the update.

 Start a binary-upload in the terminal-program and send the new firmware.
 
 If the upload is finished, the DataBox will be resetted automatically.

 @{fg shine}What to do when someting gets wrong?@{fg text}
 --------------------
 Sometimes a firmware-update could be cancelled.

 In this case set your terminal-program to 38400 Bit/s 8N1.
 Remove the socket from the DataBox for a few seconds.

 After 30 seconds you have to upload the firmware-binary.
 
 After upload is finished, teh DataBox boots with the last configuration.
@endnode

